user_prompt_template:
UPSTREAM SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE:
{upstream_system_architecture}

PROJECT CONTEXT:
Life Event: {life_event}
Audience: {audience}
Tone: {tone}

Produce the master document outline for this operational manual. One chapter per control domain from the upstream architecture. Each chapter must include a worksheet plan with 3–5 worksheet titles.

For worksheets: include a mix of types across each chapter: aim for one inventory-style worksheet (table), one checklist or compliance-verification worksheet, and 1–3 form-based planning or strategy worksheets. Do not repeat the same worksheet type more than twice in a single chapter.

Before finalising each title, ask: could this title appear unchanged in a manual for a completely different life event? If yes, rewrite it until it cannot.

Return ONLY the following JSON object. No prose. No markdown. No code fences.

{{
  "document_title": "Full manual title that names the exact life event and audience — e.g. 'The Estate Administrator Control Manual' or 'The Family Caregiver Operations Manual'",
  "document_subtitle": "A working reference system for [specific audience and life event] — not a generic tagline",
  "system_name": "Exact system_name from upstream architecture",
  "version": "1.0",
  "total_chapters": 0,
  "master_operating_rules": [
    "[Specific actionable rule for this life event] — Rationale: [why this rule exists in this specific situation]. Trigger: [the specific condition or timing that activates it]. Risk: [the concrete, named consequence of ignoring it — include a dollar amount, time penalty, or legal consequence]."
  ],
  "cascade_chain": [
    {{
      "source_domain": "Domain name from upstream architecture",
      "triggers": ["Domain name that is activated"],
      "condition": "When [specific completion or discovery in source_domain], it triggers [specific required action in the triggered domain]"
    }}
  ],
  "disclaimer_required": true,
  "introduction_text": "2–3 sentence overview specific to this life event — what this manual does, who it is for, and what capability it gives them",
  "chapters": [
    {{
      "chapter_number": 1,
      "domain_id": "domain-01",
      "domain_name": "Must match upstream control domain name exactly",
      "chapter_title": "Specific chapter title that names the operational territory — not a phase or overview. Must be specific enough that it could not appear unchanged in a different life event's manual.",
      "chapter_purpose": "One sentence: what specific operational problem this chapter solves for the reader",
      "key_topics": [
        "Specific topic derived from the upstream domain scope — must name an actual action, decision, or document involved in this life event"
      ],
      "common_gap": "The single most common and costly failure practitioners encounter in this exact domain — name the mechanism, not just the outcome",
      "cascade_triggers": [
        "When [specific output or event in this chapter] occurs, it triggers [specific required action] in [named domain]"
      ],
      "worksheet_plan": [
        {{
          "worksheet_id": "ws-01-a",
          "title": "Specific worksheet title that names the decision it enables or record it captures — cannot be generic",
          "purpose": "One sentence: the specific operational output or decision this worksheet produces",
          "section_count": 4,
          "estimated_field_count": 15
        }}
      ]
    }}
  ]
}}
